\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line The Foundation for Professional Development is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training and is accredited to offer higher education programmes by the HEQC.  Some of the programmes that are accredited are\'3A\line \'E2\'80\'A2 Certificate in Practice Management\line \'E2\'80\'A2 Certificate in Advanced Health Management\line \'E2\'80\'A2 Certificate in Risk Assessment and Management\line \'E2\'80\'A2 Diploma in Risk Assessment and Management\line \'E2\'80\'A2 Diploma in Advanced Health Management\line \'E2\'80\'A2 Postgraduate Diploma in General Practice\line The Advanced Certificate in Project Management programme served at the AC Meeting of 01 June 2011 and it was decided not to accredit the programme for the following reasons\'3A\line 1. The design of the programme and its intended outcomes are not commensurate with a level 6 offering. There is little evidence in the courseware indicating that the integrated nature of project management is pursued\'2C as the focus appears to be primarily on the content at an introductory level.\line 2. Only one part-time staff member is trained and experienced in the field of project management.\line 3. The teaching and learning strategy appears to be dominated by experiential training which negatively impacts on the balance between the theoretical and practical components that should be included.\line 4.The integrity of the assessment process is not in evidence\line 5. The library resources to support this programme appear to be inadequate.\line \line The institution submitted a representation. \cell \pard 

\intbl \row \pard 
\line \par\pard\trowd\trqc \trpaddl113\trpaddt113\trpaddb113\trpaddr113\trpaddfl3\trpaddft3\trpaddfb3\trpaddfr3\trgaph100\trrh100\trleft36
